snippet.textDisplay:
***** 

Better get your facts right !! Do not misinform music lovers. this eternal padham was recorded & performed many times by 'BharatRatna Late Smt. M.S.Subbalakshmi' in her concerts. Infact, since the black & White Video Age.

And where are the credits to the Lyricist, we can understand if one fails to trace the origin of any traditional lyrics and just leaves it at that. in this case, its a very famous kriti by a renowned 17th century telugu poet named 'kshetrayya'. he is one of the greatest poet the language ever had.

However, A Sincere Bow to 'PadmaShri Aruna Sairam' for her soulful vocal rendition to this track and very grateful to 'Ram Sampat' for choosing to do this one .. Thanks to both of them
